Envision Copyright Compliance
Introduction
This document outlines the copyright compliance for the Envision Portfolio Creator. It includes details on the proper usage and licensing of third-party materials, as well as guidelines for contributing to the project. This compliance form ensures that all content used within the project is legally sourced and appropriately credited.

Project Overview
HS Portfolio Creator is a mobile and web application designed to help high school students track and manage their extracurricular activities, generate comprehensive portfolios, and plan for college applications. The app is developed using Swift for iOS, Kotlin for Android, React for the web application, and Firebase for backend services.

Licensing
The HS Portfolio Creator app is licensed under the MIT License. This allows for broad use, modification, and distribution of the software, provided that the original copyright notice and permission notice are included in all copies or substantial portions of the software.

