Use of Third-Party Materials
The HS Portfolio Creator app may include third-party libraries, icons, and other assets. It is essential to comply with the licenses of these third-party materials. Below are the guidelines for including third-party materials in the project:

Library Inclusion:

Any third-party libraries included in the project must be open-source and compatible with the MIT License.
The license files for these libraries must be included in the repository.
Credit must be given to the authors of the third-party libraries in the README file.
Icons and Graphics:

All icons and graphics used in the project must either be created by the project team or sourced from platforms that provide assets under licenses compatible with the MIT License.
Proper attribution must be given for all third-party icons and graphics used in the project.
Attribution:

All third-party materials included in the project must be listed in the attribution section of the README file.
The attribution should include the name of the material, the author, and the license under which it is used.
Contributing to the Project
Contributors to the HS Portfolio Creator project must adhere to the following guidelines:

Original Work:

Contributions must be original work or properly licensed third-party materials.
Contributors must not include any content that infringes on the intellectual property rights of others.
License Agreement:

By contributing to the project, contributors agree to license their contributions under the MIT License.
Contributors must include a statement in their pull requests confirming that they agree to license their contributions under the MIT License.
Attribution:

Contributors must provide proper attribution for any third-party materials included in their contributions.
The attribution should be added to the appropriate section of the README file.
